FBIS3-44204 "drafr018_d_94007" FBIS-AFR-94-018 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Jan 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola President dos Santos Receives Brazilian Envoy MB2701083594 Luanda TPA Television Network in Portuguese 1930 GMT 26 Jan 94 MB2701083594 Luanda TPA Television Network Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] President of the Republic Jose Eduardo dos Santos this afternoon received a message from Brazilian President Itamar Franco. Ambassador Jose Parecido de Oliveira went to Futungo de Belas to deliver the message from the Brazilian head of state. The message notes the need and importance of creating the community of Lusophone states and also deals with issues linked to cooperation between Brazil and Angola. Ambassador Jose Parecido Oliveira told the president of the Republic that Angolans should end the absurd war that is ravaging the country and its people.
